\end_inset

 and is endogenous.
 A reasonable assumption we make is that the percentage of stockpilers does
 not change significantly with the regions.
 In any two regions A and B with populations 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{B}$
\end_inset

 respectively therefore, we would have
\begin_inset Formula $\eta p_{A}$
\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta p_{B}$
